quote_raw: He heard a distant confused yelling. Harse and the cop? But it didn't matter. The only thing that mattered was getting to the Nexus Point at one minute past one.
title: Survival Kit
author: Frederik Pohl

quote_raw: There's five fathoms out there, he said. It'll be swept up that way when the tide comes in about one. It's nine days today.
title: Ulysses
author: James Joyce

quote_raw: It was a little after one o'clock when I got there, time for lunch, so I had it. The food was awful. But it would go on the expense account, and after I'd eaten I got out my notebook and put it down. Lunch $1.50. Taxi $1.00.
title: The Big Clock
author: Kenneth Fearing
